1. modify "num_sampling" in generate_data.f90
2. download miniconda
    (a) Miniconda3 Linux 64-bit (Python version: Python 3.9)
    (b) bash ./Miniconda3-py39_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh
    (c) ~/.bashrc at the end has miniconda setup commands.
    (d) open new window
    (e) conda install numpy
    (f) conda install scikit-learn
3. (a) make gendata (build and run the executable file)
   (b) make gendata_compile (build the executable file)
   (c) data is in *.dat (ascii) and *.npy (binary) format.
4. (a) make training 
   (b) nn_coef.dat (neural network), dt_coef.dat (decision tree), and 
       rf_coef.dat (random forest) contain network weights.
5. (standalone) (a) make predict_compile
                (b) ./predict.exec
6. (integrated) (a) set ZHOUTENG_YE_ML = TRUE in GNUmakefile
                (b) search "DT_ZHOUTENG_GLOBAL" in PROB_CPP_PARMS.F90
                    for the rest.

